# Responsive Design Standards

## Rules

- Use mobile-first approach: design for mobile (360px - 430px) first, then scale up.
- Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:` (640px), `md:` (768px), `lg:` (1024px).
- Set proper viewport meta tag in HTML.
- Use responsive utilities: `px-4 md:px-8`, `text-base md:text-lg`.
- Ensure touch targets are at least 44px (min-h-[44px] or h-12).
- Use `max-w-md` for mobile containers, `max-w-7xl` for desktop.
- Maintain consistent spacing across breakpoints.
- Test on actual mobile devices when possible.

## Mobile-First Approach

- Write base styles for mobile (default, no prefix).
- Add larger screen styles with breakpoint prefixes: `md:`, `lg:`.
- Never use desktop-first approach (avoid `lg:` then base).
- Design primarily for mobile (90% of usage).

## Breakpoints

- `sm:` (640px): Small tablets, large phones.
- `md:` (768px): Tablets, small laptops.
- `lg:` (1024px): Desktop screens.
- Use breakpoints sparingly, only when necessary.
- Prefer fluid layouts over fixed breakpoints.

## Container Sizing

- Mobile: `max-w-md` (448px) centered with `mx-auto`.
- Desktop: `max-w-7xl` (1280px) for full-width layouts.
- Use `px-4` or `px-6` for mobile padding.
- Use `px-8` or `px-12` for desktop padding.

## Touch Targets

- Minimum touch target size: 44px × 44px (iOS) or 48px × 48px (Android).
- Use `min-h-[44px]` or `h-12` for buttons.
- Ensure adequate spacing between interactive elements.
- Use `gap-4` or `gap-6` for spacing between buttons.

## Typography Scaling

- Base font sizes: `text-sm` (14px), `text-base` (16px), `text-lg` (18px).
- Headings: `text-xl` (20px), `text-2xl` (24px), `text-3xl` (30px).
- Scale up for desktop: `text-base md:text-lg`, `text-2xl md:text-3xl`.
- Maintain readable line heights: `leading-normal`, `leading-relaxed`.

## Spacing Responsiveness

- Use consistent spacing scale: `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8`.
- Scale padding for larger screens: `p-4 md:p-8`.
- Use `gap-4 md:gap-6` for flex/grid gaps.
- Maintain visual hierarchy across breakpoints.

## Layout Patterns

- Stack vertically on mobile, horizontal on desktop.
- Use `flex-col md:flex-row` for responsive layouts.
- Hide/show elements with `hidden md:block` or `block md:hidden`.
- Use grid with responsive columns: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`.

