## Viewport Configuration

- Include viewport meta tag: `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />`.
- Prevent zoom on iOS inputs: ensure inputs are at least 16px font size.
- Use `user-scalable=no` only if absolutely necessary (not recommended).

## Safe Areas (iOS)

- Respect safe areas for notch and home indicator.
- Use `pb-24` or `pb-safe` for bottom padding when using fixed bottom navigation.
- Test on actual iOS devices to verify safe areas.

## Image Responsiveness

- Use responsive images: `w-full h-auto`.
- Use `object-fit` for maintaining aspect ratios.
- Provide appropriate image sizes for different breakpoints.
- Use `loading="lazy"` for images below the fold.

## Testing Guidelines

- Test on actual mobile devices (360px - 430px width).
- Test on tablets (768px width).
- Test on desktop (1024px+ width).
- Use browser DevTools responsive mode.
- Verify touch targets are accessible.

## Exceptions

- Print styles may use different breakpoints.
- Email templates may use fixed widths.
- Admin panels may prioritize desktop experience.
